<h2>Val d’Orcia (Half day / full day)</h2>
<p>
	The Val d’Orcia is classic Tuscany: rolling hills, cypress‑lined roads and picture‑perfect villages. It works brilliantly as a half‑day if you choose one stop,
	or a full day if you combine two or more towns (and allow time for a long lunch).
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day (one stop) or full day (2–4 stops)</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25–60 minutes depending on the town</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> see each stop below</li>
</ul>
<!-- Optional: replace with a temporary web photo later -->
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Val d’Orcia scenery (swap for your own photo later)" />

<h3>Montepulciano</h3>
<p>
	A lively hill town with steep streets, great viewpoints and plenty of places to stop for lunch or a wine tasting. A good “anchor” stop in the Val d’Orcia if you want a full half‑day in one place,
	or an easy pairing with Pienza.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day / full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25 minutes</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Recommended parking:</strong>{" "}
		<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/wUnm6ZSEKGh1jCsj9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps link</a>
	</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Montepulciano old town / views" />

<h3>Pienza</h3>
<p>
	A beautiful Renaissance town that’s perfect for a relaxed stroll, a coffee stop, and picking up local pecorino cheese. It’s compact and easy,
	which makes it a great half‑day option or an add‑on after Montepulciano.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~40 minutes (or ~20 minutes from Montepulciano)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Pienza streets / countryside views" />

<h3>Montalcino</h3>
<p>
	Famous for Brunello wine and big countryside views. It’s a great half‑day trip if you want a slower pace: a wander, a viewpoint, and a long lunch.
	It also pairs nicely with Pienza if you want a full day in the area.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour (or ~25 minutes from Pienza)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Montalcino views / fortress" />

<h3>Bagno Vignoni</h3>
<p>
	A tiny, unique stop built around its historic thermal waters. Even if you only spend a short time here, it’s a memorable place for photos and a gentle walk—
	great as a pairing with Pienza or Montalcino.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day (or add‑on stop)</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour (or ~20 minutes from Pienza / Montalcino)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Bagno Vignoni main square / thermal pool" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Passignano sul Trasimeno (Half day / full day)</h2>
<p>
	A relaxed lakeside town with a great promenade feel—ideal for a simple day by the water. Works as a half‑day trip on its own,
	or make it a full day by adding a longer lakeside stop (e.g. Sualzo Beach).
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day / full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~25 minutes</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Recommended parking:</strong>{" "}
		<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/NaS1AxR4L4GKNswo8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps link</a>
	</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Passignano sul Trasimeno lakeside" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Isola Maggiore (Half day)</h2>
<p>
	A great half‑day escape on Lake Trasimeno. Take the ferry over, stroll through the small lanes, and enjoy a slow lunch by the water.
	It’s an easy “holiday” feeling without a big drive.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~7 minutes to the ferry (plus ferry time)</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD — near the ferry)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Isola Maggiore waterfront" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Cortona (Half day)</h2>
<p>
	A beautiful Tuscan hill town known for views, steep streets, and a classic old‑town vibe. Great for browsing shops, a relaxed wander,
	and a long lunch if you time it right.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~30 minutes</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Cortona old town / views" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Assisi (Full day)</h2>
<p>
	One of Umbria’s most famous towns, with major basilicas, beautiful stone streets and a lot of history. Plan a full day so you can explore at a relaxed pace
	(and avoid rushing the main sights).
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour</li>
	<li>
		<strong>Recommended parking:</strong>{" "}
		<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/E7b4AsBRst5zVsoW7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps link</a>{" "}
		— easiest access, with an elevator up into Assisi
	</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Assisi basilica / town view" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Perugia (Half day / full day)</h2>
<p>
	Umbria’s capital, with lively streets, viewpoints, and plenty of places to stop for lunch or an aperitivo. Works as a half‑day,
	or a full day if you add museums and slower wandering.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Half day / full day</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~45 minutes</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Perugia historic center" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Siena (Full day / overnight)</h2>
<p>
	A classic Tuscan city for architecture, food and atmosphere—worth a full day, or even an overnight if you want to take it slower.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Full day / overnight</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~1 hour</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
<PhotoPlaceholder label="Siena streets / skyline" />

<hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid var(--border); margin: 26px 0;" />

<h2>Florence (Full day / overnight)</h2>
<p>
	A bigger trip, but unbeatable for art, shopping and iconic sights. It’s intense as a single day, so overnight can be a nicer pace if you can.
</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Type:</strong> Full day / overnight</li>
	<li><strong>Drive time:</strong> ~90 minutes</li>
	<li><strong>Recommended parking:</strong> (TBD)</li>
</ul>
